Vata Pitta Kapha
// Corpse Pose Steps 1. Lie flat on your back and relax.Legs should be separated. 2. Keep your arms at your side and your palms facing up. 3. Close your eyes and breathe deeply and slowly through the nostrils. 4. Start concentrating from your head to your feet. 5. On each inhaling and exhaling (breathing) think that your body is totally relaxed.
//Saff Pose 1. From Plank Pose, shift forward onto your tippy toes. 2. Ground through your palms and broaden across the chest. Take an inhale. 3. Bend your elbows to a 90-degree angle. Keep your thighs lifted toward the ceiling. 4. Hold your elbows in line with the torso. Gaze forward. 5. To come out of the pose, release your knees to the ground.
//Tree Pose 1. Stand with 2 inches feet apart.Focus on a point in front. 2. Bend the right leg and place the foot on the inside of the left thigh. 3. Inhale and extend the arms up and join the palms in Namaste. 4. Stay here as long as you can focusing on one point. 5. Slowly exhaling bring the arms down and then the right foot down to rest.
//Bridge Pose 1. Lye on the mat with your back on the floor. 2. Draw your feet inwards towards the hips. 3. Knees should not be pointing outwards. 4. Now lift yourself up with your stomach going towards the ceiling. 5. Chin and chest should be locked.
//Child Pose 1. Kneel on your mat with the thighs apart. 2. Sink the buttocks to the heels and curl the spine as you fold the body forward. 3. Draw the forehead down towards the ground. 4. Allow your arms to rest behind you with the palms facing up. 5. Allow the body to feel supported by the earth beneath you and breathe deeply.
//Cobra Pose 1. Lie on your abdomen with your legs spread at hip width and the tops of your feet on the floor. 2. Bend your elbows and place your palms on the floor. 3. As you inhale, press your palms against the floor. 4. Engage your back muscles, and raise your chest and head. 5.As you exhale, lower your torso and head slowly back to the floor.
//Warrior Pose 1. Stand straight and spread your legs wide-apart. 2. Turn your left feet out to face the left side of the mat. 3. The other feet will turn inward to make a 45 Degree angle 4. Twist your body to left completely.Go forward on your left knee making a 90 Degree angle 5.Go into a Namaste position,and taking arms up above your head, look up, arch your back a bit and stretch
